parameters.description: The code to run. Can be a file ID from within Shuffle.
parameters.name: code
parameters.value:
import re, json
decoded = """{{ decoded }}"""
text = (decoded or "") + "\n" + """{{ cmd }}"""
urls = re.findall(r'https?://[^\s"\'<>]+', text, flags=re.I)
ips = re.findall(r'\b(?:(?:2(?:5[0-5]|[0-4]\d))|(?:1?\d?\d))(?:\.(?:(?:2(?:5[0-5]|[0-4]\d))|(?:1?\d?\d))){3}\b', text)
hashes = re.findall(r'\b[a-f0-9]{64}\b', text, flags=re.I)
print(json.dumps({"urls": list(set(urls)), "ips": list(set(ips)), "hashes": list(set(hashes))}))
